title: Japanese Prints at the Art Institute of Chicago Postcard Book
description:
More than 350 years of printmaking and dozens of artists are represented in this selection of Japanese works at the Art Institute of Chicago. Figures, landscapes, and abstract images showcase techniques ranging from woodblock to silkscreen and provide an enticing introduction to the museum’s world-renowned print collection.

Includes 31 colored postcards.

6.5 in. x 4.75 in.
